name: Joel Costigliola
message:
Deprecate Java 6/Android assertions entry point. Fixes #1474.

The goal of these entry points was to provide Java6/Android compatible assertions but since we have moved to Java 8 it became more complicated, filtering out java 8 types is not sufficient as we have refactored some assertions implementation to use lambdas and streams that made them improper to use in Java 6. Reverting all this work is not worth it as Android is moving to have more java 8 support.

name: Joel Costigliola
message:
Recursive comparison breaking changes: use of the expected field as a reference for container type compatibility
- sorted vs non sorted are replaced ordered vs unordered semantics (ordered type are List, SortedSet and LinkedHashSet)
- actual ordered vs expected unordered is allowed but actual unordered vs expected ordered is not

Refactor RecursiveComparisonDifferenceCalculator:
- introduce ComparisonState
- remove quite a bit of code duplication

Improve error messages when group size differs or when trying to compare actual unordered vs expected ordered.

Split and add a bunch of tests.
